title: WATCH: Gabriel Jesus Scores His First Manchester City Goal
text:
WATCH: Gabriel Jesus Scores His First Manchester City Goal Wed Feb 01 2017 21:20:00   21:20:00   
He's been a Manchester City player for a matter of weeks, but Gabriel Jesus already looks every inch the superstar that he's already being touted as, and he celebrated his first goal for the club tonight. 
Having started his first game for the club in the 3-0 win over Crystal Palace in the FA Cup at the weekend, Jesus was kept in the team by Pep Guardiola for tonight's Premiership clash against West Ham, and the Brazilian certainly didn't disappoint. 
Looking lively and energetic, the 19-year-old's enthusiasm helped set-up team-mate Kevin de Bruyne for the game's opening goal, before grabbing one of his own before half-time: Gabriel Jesus' first goal for Manchester City pic.twitter.com/GTwnrZqQnx - Brazil Edition Vids (@BE_Videos) February 1, 2017 
That means, in less than three games for the Sky Blues, Jesus already has one goal and two assists for his new club. 
Not at all bad for a teenager, eh? 
Then the cameras panned to Aguero who didn't exactly look thrilled for the Brazilian forward... Aguero looks pretty excited for Gabriel Jesus @MenInBlazers pic.twitter.com/Ru0bcKgxR6 - connor (@Connor Dowling) <a href=" https://twitter.com/Connor Dowling/status/826890122629173249">February 1, 2017 
Just look at his face... 
What do you think of Jesus's early impression on English football? How impressed have you been?
